original: Jonsson, Ernst Bertil Ragnar, ingenjör, Skövde, f. 27/1/04 i Örebro av Ernst Henrik J. o. Maria Liljeqvist. G. m. Elisabeth Ahlin. Barn: Monica f. 34, Per-Henrik 47. — Realex. i Örebro 21, tekn. gymn. där 26. Res. i Tvskl o. Tjeckoslov. 38. Anst. bl. a. v. A-B Bofors 33i-40, v. Nydqvist & Holm A-B 40-42, chef f. beredn:-avd. v. A-B Volvo-Pen taverken i Skövde fr. 42, Medl av Tekn. fören. i Skövde fr. 43. Hobby: friluftsliv.
translated: Jonsson, Ernst Bertil Ragnar, engineer, Skövde, b. January 27, 1904 in Örebro to Ernst Henrik J. and Maria Liljeqvist. Married to Elisabeth Ahlin in an unspecified year. Children: Monica, b. 1934 and Per-Henrik, b. 1947. Completed Realexamen in Örebro in 1921 and tekniskt gymnasium in 1926. Traveled to Switzerland and Czechoslovakia in 1938. Employed by A-B Bofors from 1931-1940, Nydqvist & Holm A-B from 1940-1942, and was the head of the preparatory department at A-B Volvo-Pentaverken in Skövde from 1942 onwards. Became a member of the Tekniska föreningen in Skövde in 1943. Hobby: outdoor activities.
